---
import Layout from "./layout.astro";
import Header from "@/components/Header.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <slot name="header">
    <Header />
    <blockquote
      class="border-l-2 pl-4 text-lg italic font-semibold text-gray-900/65 dark:text-white/65"
    >
      <svg
        class="w-4 h-4 text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-600 mb-2"
        aria-hidden="true"
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        fill="currentColor"
        viewBox="0 0 18 14"
      >
        <path
          d="M6 0H2a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v4a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h4v1a3 3 0 0 1-3 3H2a1 1 0 0 0 0 2h1a5.006 5.006 0 0 0 5-5V2a2 2 0 0 0-2-2Zm10 0h-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v4a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h4v1a3 3 0 0 1-3 3h-1a1 1 0 0 0 0 2h1a5.006 5.006 0 0 0 5-5V2a2 2 0 0 0-2-2Z"
        ></path>
      </svg>
      <p class="font-['Montserrat'] font-thin">
        At each stage do whatever seems most interesting and gives you the best
        options for the future. I call this approach "staying upwind." This is
        how most people who've done great work seem to have done it.
      </p>
    </blockquote>
  </slot>

  <main>
    <br />
    <h2
      class="text-sm tracking-wider leading-loose uppercase text-white/45 font-bold font-sans"
    >
      posts
    </h2>
    <slot />
  </main>
</Layout>
